## Project Context
- Stack: Next.js + TypeScript (FE), Express + TypeScript (BE), Neon PostgreSQL
- TipTap: store content as `JSONContent` (never HTML in DB); render via TipTap's HTML output
- Auth: import `authenticate` from `authentication-engineer`'s middleware — never rewrite it
- API prefix: `/api/v1/`

## Article Status Machine (you own ALL transitions)
```
                    ┌──────────────────────────────────────────┐
                    │                                          │
  POST /articles    ▼      POST /submit        PATCH /approve  │
  ──────────────► [Draft] ────────────────► [Pending] ──────► [Published]
                    ▲                            │
                    │       PATCH /reject        │
                    └────────────────────────── [Rejected]
                         (author edits → auto-reset to Draft)
```

| From | Action | To | Who |
|------|--------|-----|-----|
| — | Create | Draft | Author |
| Draft | Submit for Review | Pending | Author |
| Pending | Approve | Published | Reviewer/Admin (via `content-moderation-engineer`) |
| Pending | Reject + feedback | Rejected | Reviewer/Admin (via `content-moderation-engineer`) |
| Rejected | Author edits | Draft (auto-reset) | Author (auto) |
| Draft | Author deletes | (deleted) | Author |
| Any | Admin soft-delete | deleted_at set | Admin |
| Any | Admin hard-delete | Row removed | Admin |

## Strict Rules
1. `Pending → Published / Rejected` are SET via `articleRepository.updateStatus()`, called from `content-moderation-engineer`'s `ReviewService` — coordinate on this interface, don't duplicate the transition logic on their side.
2. Article ownership: always verify `article.authorId === req.user.userId` before edit/delete.
3. Hard delete is Admin-only; soft delete (`deleted_at`) for everyone else.
4. Author can only delete Draft articles.
5. Editing a Rejected article auto-resets status to Draft.
6. Never touch auth, comments, likes, or quiz (other roles' domains).
7. Never touch notifications, review-decision logic, or tech-talk management (other roles' domains).

```typescript
// src/services/articleService.ts
private assertTransition(current: ArticleStatus, next: ArticleStatus, role: UserRole): void {
  const allowed: Record<ArticleStatus, ArticleStatus[]> = {
    Draft: ['Pending'],
    Pending: ['Published', 'Rejected'],
    Published: [],
    Rejected: ['Draft'],
  };
  const reviewerActions = ['Published', 'Rejected'];
  if (reviewerActions.includes(next) && !['Reviewer', 'Admin'].includes(role)) {
    throw new AppError('Only Reviewers can approve or reject articles', 403);
  }
  if (!allowed[current]?.includes(next)) {
    throw new AppError(`Cannot transition from ${current} to ${next}`, 400);
  }
}

async editArticle(id: string, updates: ArticleUpdateInput, userId: string): Promise<Article> {
  const article = await this.findOwned(id, userId);
  const editableStatuses: ArticleStatus[] = ['Draft', 'Rejected'];
  if (!editableStatuses.includes(article.status)) {
    throw new AppError('Only Draft or Rejected articles can be edited', 400);
  }
  const newStatus: ArticleStatus = article.status === 'Rejected' ? 'Draft' : article.status;
  return articleRepository.update(id, { ...updates, status: newStatus });
}

private async findOwned(articleId: string, userId: string): Promise<Article> {
  const article = await articleRepository.findById(articleId);
  if (!article) throw new AppError('Article not found', 404);
  if (article.authorId !== userId) throw new AppError('Not authorized', 403);
  return article;
}
```

## List Endpoints
- `GET /api/v1/articles` — list published, with `?sort=title|created_at`, `?order=asc|desc`, `?search=keyword` (ILIKE on title), `?page=1&limit=20`. Always apply `status = 'Published' AND deleted_at IS NULL`.
- `GET /api/v1/articles/mine` — all statuses for the authenticated user, includes `reviewer_feedback` so the author can see rejection reasons.

## Rich Text Storage
```typescript
// src/lib/tiptap.ts
import { generateText } from '@tiptap/core';
import StarterKit from '@tiptap/starter-kit';

export function extractTextFromTipTap(json: JSONContent): string {
  return generateText(json, [StarterKit]);
}
```
`extractTextFromTipTap` is consumed by `ai-integration-engineer`'s quiz generator — keep its signature stable.

```tsx
// src/components/articles/ArticleEditor.tsx — shared, never duplicate
interface ArticleEditorProps {
  initialContent?: JSONContent;
  onChange: (content: JSONContent) => void;
  readOnly?: boolean;
}
```

## Delete Rules
| Deleter | Target Status | Action |
|---------|--------------|--------|
| Author | Draft only | Soft delete (`deleted_at = NOW()`) |
| Admin | Any status | Soft delete by default; hard delete available |

All delete actions require a `<ConfirmationModal>` (shared component).

